{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the Luxury Car Tax threshold to \u00a350-55,000",
        "additional_details": "It has been reported that the current average value for a new vehicle in the UK is around \u00a340,000, which is the current threshold for luxury car tax. We believe it\u2019s wrong that the reported average in the UK has become a luxury and should be increased. We feel hardworking people deserve to not be overly taxed on the average and that the threshold should be raised to \u00a350k-\u00a355k, as this could be more reflective of what was defined as luxury.",
        "background": "We believe the Government should raise increase the value threshold of Luxury car tax to above the average new vehicle value. We believe the AVERAGE should NOT be a luxury.",
